==English==
===Etymology 1===
From Latin ''pro'', "on [[behalf]] of."

===Pronunciation===
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-əʊ|-əʊ]]

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}

# an [[advantage]] of something, especially when contrasted with its [[disadvantage]]s (''[[con]]s'').
#:''pros and cons''

====Prefix====
'''pro''' (often hyphenated)

#In favor of.

====Related terms====
*[[pros and cons]]

===Etymology 2===
*Shortened from ''[[professional]]''.

====Noun====
'''pro''' (''plural'' '''pros''')

# a professional sportsman
# {{colloquial}} someone who is very good at something
#:''When it comes to [[DIY]], he's a real '''pro'''.''

====Related terms====
*[[pro-am]]

===Etymology 3===
*Shortened from ''[[prostitute]]''.

====Noun====
{{en-noun-reg}}

# {{slang}} a [[prostitute]]

